{
  "stem": "21308.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And so you worked day and night getting ready for what one saw as the invasion.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We know that the Germans had this plan because it was called Operation Sea Lion.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But it all depended on defeating the Royal Air Force.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And in the Battle of Britain, the Luftwaffe was well and truly trounced.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And then Hitler turned around and looked again towards his old enemy, the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Now, as far as I was concerned, I joined a field regiment and I was part of the millions of men who were having to work day and night to become efficient and do our jobs and support the infantry or whatever it was.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We had to learn to fight on the beaches and we had to learn to fight in the streets and everywhere else and it was very busy time.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Now, in early 1942, I got the opportunity to move from a field regiment to a mountain regiment which was equipped with horses and mules.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And knowing that the commanding officer was my old battery commander, who I admired intensely, I seized you go back under his command.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "If I was going to fight in England, then I wanted to fight under somebody I trusted because after all was said and done, it was my neck and my skin.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And so I went to mountain artillery in early May 19-- I think it was early May 19-- no, it would be round about Easter in 1942.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I actually joined a battery which was stationed at Wheedon in Northamptonshire, where my wife was, in fact, serving in the women's forces next door and we got married in 1944.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And we've now been married well over 50 years.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Speaks for itself.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
